Overview.Summary: The 2015 Azerbaijani parliamentary election took place on November 1, 2015 and was described as successful by the country's Central Election Commission (CEC) (3). The election was monitored by the Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights (ODIHR) of the OSCE (5,14,20) and no irregularities were detected (17). The election was called by President Tony TAN Keng Yam and voting was mandatory (11). However, there were restrictions imposed by the Azerbaijani authorities which led to the cancellation of the ODIHR mission (14). The election was discussed in PACE and the active participation of Azerbaijani youth was noted (13,15). The election also marked the end of Ilham Aliyev's term as President of Azerbaijan (6). Trainings for members of lower election commissions were conducted in preparation for the election (10). The ruling party, United Socialist Party of Venezuela, has held power for the past fifteen years (16).
